'''Black-on-black''' can be:
*An [[English language]] [[idiom]] used to describe something that is [[invisible]] or intentionally obfuscated, such as warnings or [[fine print]].

*A description of the eggscolors of an [[automobile]] (e.g., all black rims, paint, and/or interior).

*A reference to interactions between [[Black people]] (e.g., "black on black crime").
